Function reference

Manual layer

These are manually written/curated functions which wrap some of the key calls into the OpenAPI autogen layer. They’re more user-friendly and better documented. See also the Article on Package Status.

array_info()
Show information about an array on TileDB Cloud
compute()
Launch a task graph from a given terminal node in the task graph
compute_sequentially()
Test/debug entrypoint for local/sequential compute.
configure()
Configure TileDB Cloud
delayed()
Define a function to be executed within a task graph
`delayed_args<-`()
Set arguments for a delayed function.
delayed_args()
Get arguments for a delayed function, as a list.
delayed_array_udf()
Define a single-array UDF to be executed within a task graph
delayed_generic_udf()
Define a generic UDF to be executed within a task graph
delayed_sql()
Define a SQL query function to be executed within a task graph
deregister_array()
Deregister an array from TileDB Cloud
deregister_udf()
Deregister a UDF from TileDB Cloud
execute_array_udf()
Execute a single-array UDF on TileDB Cloud
execute_generic_udf()
Execute a generic UDF on TileDB Cloud
execute_multi_array_udf()
Execute a multi-array UDF on TileDB Cloud
execute_sql_query()
Execute a SQL query on TileDB Cloud
get_api_client_instance()
Access cached API-client object
get_udf_info()
Get information about a UDF on TileDB Cloud
list_arrays()
Show listing of arrays
login()
Log in to TileDB Cloud
register_array()
Register an existing array on TileDB Cloud
register_udf()
Register a UDF on TileDB Cloud
update_udf_info()
Update a UDF on TileDB Cloud
user_profile()
Show information from user TileDB Cloud user profile

Package-internal layer

These are functions intended to be invoked by the manual-layer functions, as implementation details beneath the interest of most users of the API.

.get_decoded_response_body_or_stop()
Package-internal HTTP-response helper
.get_empty_response_body_or_stop()
Package-internal HTTP-response helper
.get_raw_response_body_or_stop()
Package-internal HTTP-response helper
.wrap_as_api_response()
Package-internal HTTP-response helper
